# Phase 3.3: Booking Module Migration Plan (Revised)

## Goal

Migrate the Booking module to Clean Architecture using the proven copy-first strategy from Phase 3.2.  
The booking state machine, payment cross-dependency, real-time socket events, Telegram alerts, and chat must remain **functionally identical** throughout and after migration.

---

## 1. Dependency Analysis

### 1.1 Direct Importers of `models/Booking.js`

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `src/controllers/bookingController.js` | Core CRUD + state machine (7 actions) |
| `src/controllers/paymentController.js` | Reads booking for order creation + verifies status before wallet settlement |
| `src/controllers/review.js` | Reads booking to validate `status === 'completed'` before accepting a review |
| `src/services/telegramService.js` | Reads booking to dispatch Telegram alert on new booking |
| `src/services/reminderService.js` | Reads and writes booking during 60s auto-timeout |
| `src/modules/worker/infrastructure/persistence/repositories/MongoBookingRepository.js` | Dashboard: active bookings for worker |
| `src/modules/worker/infrastructure/persistence/repositories/MongoPaymentRepository.js` | Dashboard: payment lookup by booking IDs |
| `tests/bookingStateMachine.test.js` | 14 state machine integration tests |
| `tests/paymentRedirect.test.js` | Payment flow integration tests |

### 1.2 Direct Importers of `routes/booking.js`

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `src/index.js` | Mounts at `/api/v1/bookings` |
| `tests/bookingStateMachine.test.js` | Builds test Express app with legacy routes |
| `tests/paymentRedirect.test.js` | Builds test Express app with legacy routes |

