## 3. [NEW] State Machine Compatibility Verification

After deploying the proxy wrapper (`models/Booking.js` ŌåÆ `BookingSchema.js`), all state machine transitions must be verified against the **legacy routes** (which remain active throughout Phase 3.3).

### 3.1 Valid Transitions (must all return `200` or `201`)

| # | From | Endpoint | To | Expected |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | ŌĆö | `POST /api/v1/bookings` | `pending` | `201` |
| 2 | `pending` | `PUT /:id/accept` | `accepted` | `200` + `booking.status === 'accepted'` |
| 3 | `accepted` | `PUT /:id/start` | `in_progress` | `200` + `booking.status === 'in_progress'` |
| 4 | `in_progress` | `PUT /:id/complete` | `completed` | `200` + `booking.status === 'completed'` |
| 5 | `completed` | `POST /payments/verify` (mock) | `paid` | `200` + `booking.status === 'paid'` + `paymentStatus === 'paid'` |
| 6 | `pending` | `PUT /:id/cancel` | `cancelled` | `200` + no `metadata.cancellationFee` |
| 7 | `accepted` | `PUT /:id/cancel` | `cancelled` | `200` + `metadata.cancellationFee.amount === 50` |

### 3.2 Invalid Transitions (must all return `400`)

| # | From | Endpoint | Attempted To | Expected |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 8 | `pending` | `PUT /:id/start` | `in_progress` | `400` ŌĆö cannot skip accepted |
| 9 | `accepted` | `PUT /:id/complete` | `completed` | `400` ŌĆö must be in_progress first |
| 10 | `in_progress` | `POST /payments/verify` | `paid` | `400` ŌĆö must be completed |
| 11 | `completed` | `PUT /:id/cancel` | `cancelled` | `400` ŌĆö completed cannot be cancelled |

### 3.3 Blocked Worker Guard (must return `403`)

| # | Precondition | Endpoint | Expected |
|---|---|---|---|
| 12 | Worker `isBlocked: true` | `PUT /:id/accept` | `403` with `'blocked'` in error message |
| 13 | Worker `isBlocked: true` | `PUT /:id` (profile) `{ isAvailable: true }` | `403` with `'Blocked workers'` in error message |

**Coverage:** All 13 scenarios above are already covered by `tests/bookingStateMachine.test.js`. Verification = running that test suite. Zero new test code is required.

